# Parent Information

Everything you need to know to prepare your camper for an amazing week at Camp Otyokwah in Butler, Ohio.

## Check-In & Check-Out

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="Clock"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Check-In Times"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
**Sunday Afternoon** at Hopewell Hall

Please arrive during the designated check-in window so we can properly welcome your camper and get them settled into their cabin.

*Pioneer Camp check-in is Thursday morning — see your session confirmation for specific times.*
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Car"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Pick-Up Times"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
**Friday Evening** after our closing program for all overnight sessions.

**Saturday Morning** pick-up may be available for select sessions — see your session details.

Check out your camper at their cabin and collect their belongings before you leave.

Please arrive on time — counselors are released when all campers are picked up.
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

## What Happens at Check-In

{% sectionCard variant="default" background="none" width="auto" %}
When you arrive at Hopewell Hall, you will:

1. **Check in at the registration table**
1. **Settle your account balance**
1. **Turn in all medications to the camp nurse** (in original containers with dosage instructions)
1. **Receive your cabin assignment**
1. **Head to the cabin to meet your counselor and choose a bed**
1. **Say your goodbyes before opening program begins**

*Pro tip: Arrive a few minutes early to walk around, see the facilities, and ask any last-minute questions!*
{% /sectionCard %}

