## Health Forms & Medical Information

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="ClipboardList"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Health Forms"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
Health forms are completed during online registration through UltraCamp. Please:

- Complete all health history fields accurately
- List all allergies and medical conditions
- Include your primary care physician's contact information
- Note any dietary restrictions so we can accommodate your camper
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Pill"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Medication Policy"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- Turn in **all medications** to the nurse at check-in
- Medications must be in **original containers** with pharmacy labels
- Include **written dosage instructions**
- Nurse dispenses all medications on schedule
- Campers may NOT keep medications in cabins (exceptions for rescue inhalers and certain medical devices)
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

## Staying Connected

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="MessageCircle"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Communication Policy"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
Part of what makes camp transformative is the focused, distraction-free environment during the week. Our camp program is screen-free.

- Campers do not have access to phones during camp
- If you need to reach your camper for an emergency, call the camp office and leave a message
- Leadership staff will facilitate a call home if your camper is struggling
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Camera"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Regular Updates"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
We'll keep you in the loop!

- **Photos posted** on our social media pages throughout the week
- You're welcome to send letters or care packages (no food please)
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

## Write to Your Camper

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="Mail"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Snail Mail"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
Our campers love to get mail at camp! Send letters, postcards, or packages to:

**[Camper Name]**
**Camp Otyokwah**
**3380 Tugend Rd**
**Butler, OH 44822**

*Mail sent Monday or Tuesday will typically arrive before camp ends.*
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Gift"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Care Package Tips"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Do** send encouraging notes, stickers, small items
- **Do** include stamps and addressed postcards
- **Don't** send food (dietary reasons and cabin critters!)
- **Don't** send expensive items that could get lost
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

## Pray for Your Camper

{% sectionCard variant="elevated" background="none" width="auto" %}
We believe **PRAYER** is a vital part of the ministry at Camp Otyokwah. You are encouraged to pray throughout the day.

**Pray daily that your camper and others will:**

- Be **CHANGED** by encountering Jesus
- Make a **decision to GROW** in their faith
- Be **EQUIPPED** to read and engage Scripture
- Build **healthy relationships** with others
- Experience the **love of God**
- Sense **God's presence** daily
- Enjoy a **fun, safe week**

Also pray for your camper's specific needs and for our camp staff!
{% /sectionCard %}

## Health & Safety

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="Stethoscope"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Medical Care"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Trained staff on-site** during all camp hours
- All staff trained in First Aid and CPR
- We'll contact you for any health concerns
- Hospital accessible from our Butler, Ohio location
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Shield"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Safety Policies"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- All activity areas supervised by trained staff
- Waterfront activities include certified lifeguard supervision
- Climbing wall and zip line operated by trained facilitators
- Background-checked counselors and staff
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

